The crowd round a couple of dogs fighting, is a crowd masculine mainly, with an occasional active, compassionate woman, fluttering wildly round the outside‚ and using her tongue and her hands freely upon the men, as so many ‘brutes 3’ it is a crowd annulat, compact, and mo bile3 a crowd centripetal, having its eyes and its heads all bent downwards and inwards, to one com- mon focus.

Well, Bob and I are up, and find it is not over: a small thoroughbred, white bull-terrier, is busy throttling a large shepherd’s dog, unaccustomed to ’ war, but not to be trifled with. They are hard at it ; the scientific little fellow doing his work in great style, his pastoral enemy fighting wildly, but with the sharpest of teeth and a great courage.
